The Cross River State’s Integrated Bakassi Deep Seaport project inched towards reality yesterday with the opening of bid for itsconstruction. Port of Antwerp International of Belgium and CPCS Transcom of Canada were the two main bidders. The event, which took place at the conference room of the State Planning Commission, Calabar had the bidders participating  virtually through zoom from Belgium and Canada. The bid opening was witnessed by the Calabar Chamber of Commerce and Industry represented by Kenneth Asim Ituah and the Civil Society Organisations represented by Mrs Glory Patrick Etokeren of Budget Transparency and Accountability Network, BTAN. Speaking at the event, Chairman Steering Committee for the Integrated Bakassi Deep seaport project, Dr. Francis Ntamu assured that the project would not suffer abandonment. According to Ntamu who is also the Chief Economic Adviser to Governor Ben Ayade, the Public Private Partnership (PPP) model of the seaport   project has completely eliminated uncertainty about its completion.  